<b>Lifestyle Changes To Prevent Vertigo</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">These are some things you can do to help relieve your condition:</span>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> ¬†</span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">If the vertigo attack comes, calmly sit down, turn off the TV, and keep calm until the attack subsides.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> ¬†</span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Avoid driving during the period of attack: if the attack happens when you‚Äôre driving, pull over immediately and rest until the attack is over.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> ¬†</span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Eat at regular times. Low level of sugar in the blood can cause vertigo.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> ¬†</span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Reduce or totally avoid your caffeine intake. It has been proved to increase the development of vertigo.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> ¬†</span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Reduce/stop alcohol: Alcohol can cause dizziness. Pairing that with Vertigo may mean double trouble.</span></li>
</ul>
<b>Going beyond in the holistic approach</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Traditional western methods are widely used for treating Vertigo, Louise Hay, Motivational leader and empowerment coach who has done pathbreaking work in supporting HIV/AIDS patients and their families, has said that, ‚ÄúIllness however mild or severe is an indicator of your emotional state, caused by your thoughts and focus.‚Äù</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to her, the main cause of Vertigo is:</span><b> Flighty, scattered thinking. </b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the ways of healing this is through saying or writing affirmations. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Her affirmation for healing Vertigo is: </span><b>I am deeply centered and peaceful in life. I am safe for me to be alive and joyous.</b>

